1️⃣ Subnetting (Numerical Understanding 🔥)
Simple Idea

Subnetting = divide IP network into smaller parts

Example Question

👉 IP: 192.168.1.0/24
How many hosts possible?

Concept Formula

Number of hosts
=
2
𝑛
−
2
Number of hosts=2
n
−2

Where:

n = number of host bits
Solve

/24 means:

32 – 24 = 8 host bits

So:

2^8 - 2 = 254 hosts
Why “-2”?
1 for network address
1 for broadcast address
Memory Trick 🧠

2ⁿ – 2 → always remember

2️⃣ Subnetting Trick (Fast Method)
Question

Divide /24 into 4 subnets

Trick

👉 4 = 2² → borrow 2 bits

New subnet:

/24 + 2 = /26
Subnets
192.168.1.0
192.168.1.64
192.168.1.128
192.168.1.192
Why It Works

Each subnet gets equal range.

Memory Trick

Subnets = 2ⁿ → borrow n bits

